WEBVTT

1
00:01:54.239 --> 00:01:55.531
Pretty windy out.

2
00:01:55.698 --> 00:01:58.367
[MIMICS EXPLOSIONS]

3
00:02:06.500 --> 00:02:08.544
That better not be the one
where you blow people up.

4
00:02:08.711 --> 00:02:11.213
It's not, Mom.

5
00:02:11.881 --> 00:02:13.215
Uh-huh.

6
00:02:15.175 --> 00:02:17.177
Dad, look what I can do.

7
00:02:17.844 --> 00:02:19.387
I've been practicing.

8
00:02:23.350 --> 00:02:26.394
-That's spectacular, kiddo.
CHARLIE: Cool.

9
00:02:26.561 --> 00:02:27.979
[CLEARS THROAT]

10
00:02:29.689 --> 00:02:31.858
You're inside out.

11
00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:37.238
Oh. I knew that.
Doesn't work for you?

12
00:02:38.239 --> 00:02:44.120
-I can't believe you taught him that.
-Ha, ha, ha. I didn't. He did it on his own.

13
00:02:45.080 --> 00:02:48.041
-Charlie, did you brush your teeth?
-Yes.

14
00:02:48.249 --> 00:02:50.377
-Charlie.
-I brushed them.

15
00:02:51.086 --> 00:02:54.547
EDWARD: Look at this, Con.
-Let's go. I'm serious.

16
00:02:54.714 --> 00:02:57.759
CHARLIE:
You're driving me bonkers, Mom.

17
00:02:57.926 --> 00:02:59.386
CONNIE:
Let's go.

18
00:02:59.552 --> 00:03:02.764
Remember when you said no
to buying Omnidell?

19
00:03:02.931 --> 00:03:06.518
-Remember what the price was?
CONNIE: One-fifty.

20
00:03:07.394 --> 00:03:09.229
Close.
Sixty-one.

21
00:03:09.437 --> 00:03:11.814
-I’ll do it, Mom.
-No, I'll do it.

22
00:03:12.064 --> 00:03:14.066
You know what it's going for now?

23
00:03:14.274 --> 00:03:15.901
-Say "E"
CHARLIE: E.

24
00:03:16.402 --> 00:03:21.156
-Guess, Con.
-Edward, I don't know, all right?

25
00:03:21.407 --> 00:03:23.450
-Now rinse.
-Seventy-four.

26
00:03:23.659 --> 00:03:25.451
Really rinse.
And pee.

27
00:03:26.035 --> 00:03:29.038
Seventy-four. Should have bought it.
Shit.

28
00:03:29.539 --> 00:03:33.251
CONNIE: So buy some.
EDWARD: Too late, Con. Too late.

29
00:03:33.751 --> 00:03:36.045
Lift the seat, honey.

30
00:03:39.798 --> 00:03:42.300
Don't forget to put it down.

31
00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:45.971
When you finish.

32
00:03:48.640 --> 00:03:54.646
-Do you really need all that stuff?
-Mom, no one wears these dorky hats.

33
00:03:54.980 --> 00:03:58.357
-You do and you're not a dork.
-How do I look?

34
00:03:58.607 --> 00:04:00.984
Very handsome.

35
00:04:01.860 --> 00:04:04.946
Love you.
Okay, come on, let's go.

36
00:04:05.113 --> 00:04:07.490
Whoa.
Jesus.

37
00:04:08.074 --> 00:04:09.284
Come on.

38
00:04:09.451 --> 00:04:12.203
-Whoa.
-Maybe you shouldn't go in.

39
00:04:12.454 --> 00:04:16.207
I have stuff to do for the auction.
And there's a birthday soon.

40
00:04:16.458 --> 00:04:20.211
Latrell Sprewell jersey, Mom.
Don't forget.

41
00:04:20.503 --> 00:04:26.009
-He's on the Yankees, right?
-Mom, you're driving me bonkers.

42
00:04:26.176 --> 00:04:29.220
You're driving him bonkers.

43
00:04:33.183 --> 00:04:34.975
Jesus.

44
00:04:35.184 --> 00:04:37.686
[INDISTINCT DIALOGUE ON TV]

45
00:05:29.738 --> 00:05:31.907
[WIND HOWLING]

46
00:05:48.465 --> 00:05:49.967
Ugh.

47
00:05:57.474 --> 00:05:59.268
Oh!

48
00:06:04.815 --> 00:06:06.441
[SCREAMS]

49
00:06:08.193 --> 00:06:11.822
Taxi!
Shit.

50
00:06:12.447 --> 00:06:14.700
Taxi!

51
00:06:15.576 --> 00:06:17.744
Taxi!
Taxi!

52
00:06:25.459 --> 00:06:27.003
[HORN HONKING]

53
00:06:30.214 --> 00:06:31.966
[GRUNTING]

54
00:06:44.812 --> 00:06:46.355
[GRUNTING]

55
00:06:50.318 --> 00:06:52.778
[BOTH GRUNTING]

56
00:06:55.489 --> 00:06:57.491
PAUL: Whoa!
-I'm so sorry.

57
00:06:57.658 --> 00:06:58.993
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

58
00:06:59.160 --> 00:07:00.494
I'm so sorry.

59
00:07:00.661 --> 00:07:02.121
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

60
00:07:03.623 --> 00:07:04.999
CONNIE:
I'm sorry.

61
00:07:05.750 --> 00:07:07.835
PAUL:
I'll get your things.

62
00:07:12.840 --> 00:07:14.634
Fuck!
Shit!

63
00:07:17.845 --> 00:07:20.264
Taxi!
Taxi!

64
00:07:20.473 --> 00:07:22.141
My books.

65
00:07:22.683 --> 00:07:24.977
[PAUL SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

66
00:07:35.655 --> 00:07:39.867
-Could you help me get a taxi?
PAUL: Okay.

67
00:07:40.326 --> 00:07:42.411
CONNIE: I'll watch your books.
-Thanks.

68
00:07:42.578 --> 00:07:43.662
CONNIE:
Thank you.

69
00:07:46.414 --> 00:07:49.209
Hey.
Hey!

70
00:07:51.544 --> 00:07:52.545
Hey.

71
00:07:52.712 --> 00:07:53.755
[HORN HONKING]

72
00:07:53.922 --> 00:07:55.048
[SCREAMS]

73
00:07:59.761 --> 00:08:00.845
[HORN HONKING]

74
00:08:05.392 --> 00:08:08.520
-Bad day for taxis.
-It's this horrible wind.

75
00:08:09.062 --> 00:08:11.898
Yeah, you shot down there
like a bullet!

76
00:08:12.107 --> 00:08:14.692
If you flapped your arms,
you'd be home now.

77
00:08:14.858 --> 00:08:17.903
I'll remember that next time.

78
00:08:18.904 --> 00:08:21.448
-That's not good.
-I know.

79
00:08:21.740 --> 00:08:26.412
Listen, that's me up there.
The flowerpot.

80
00:08:27.704 --> 00:08:30.581
I’ll get you a Band-Aid, okay?

81
00:08:33.459 --> 00:08:36.754
Hold onto something.
Don't blow away.

82
00:08:38.464 --> 00:08:43.052
Or you can come on up
and clean it off, no?

83
00:08:43.386 --> 00:08:45.221
Come on.

84
00:08:45.430 --> 00:08:49.100
I'm not an ax murderer.
I promise.

85
00:09:00.570 --> 00:09:01.612
Oh, shit.

86
00:09:03.406 --> 00:09:04.657
Fucking elevator.

87
00:09:04.866 --> 00:09:06.784
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

88
00:09:11.789 --> 00:09:13.583
One more.

89
00:09:34.687 --> 00:09:38.816
-Pardon the mess.
-Are you a writer?

90
00:09:40.276 --> 00:09:42.487
-I'm a book dealer.
-Oh.

91
00:09:45.323 --> 00:09:48.785
Bathroom's right down there,
on the left.

92
00:09:51.037 --> 00:09:54.998
Go ahead.
There's a medicine cabinet.

93
00:09:55.165 --> 00:09:58.918
You can sneak a peek
at my prescriptions.

94
00:10:20.022 --> 00:10:21.232
[CONNIE GASPS]

95
00:10:27.196 --> 00:10:28.780
Ugh.

96
00:11:05.859 --> 00:11:07.777
Hello?

97
00:11:17.704 --> 00:11:21.708
-I made you some tea.
-Thank you.

98
00:11:22.876 --> 00:11:27.755
-Do you box?
-I used to, when I was young.

99
00:11:27.922 --> 00:11:29.257
Hm....

100
00:11:30.049 --> 00:11:32.093
This is an amazing place.

101
00:11:32.260 --> 00:11:35.722
-Yeah, but it's not mine.
-No?

102
00:11:36.097 --> 00:11:39.266
The owner is a friend, a sculptor.
He's in Paris.

103
00:11:39.433 --> 00:11:43.937
That's cool.
We can stay here, me and my books.

104
00:11:45.521 --> 00:11:46.897
Hm.

105
00:11:47.314 --> 00:11:51.943
Can I use your phone?
I have to call home.

106
00:11:52.152 --> 00:11:54.779
Sure, there's a phone just behind you.

107
00:11:55.030 --> 00:11:56.906
Thank you.

108
00:12:02.411 --> 00:12:04.455
Gloria?
Hi, it's me.

109
00:12:04.955 --> 00:12:08.542
Good, good.
How's Charlie?

110
00:12:08.751 --> 00:12:11.587
Hi, honey.
How was your day at school?

111
00:12:11.795 --> 00:12:14.964
Yeah?
What was the best part?

112
00:12:15.131 --> 00:12:18.927
Guess what? Can you believe it?
Mommy missed her train.

113
00:12:19.427 --> 00:12:20.470
Um....

114
00:12:25.641 --> 00:12:27.141
Ice.

115
00:12:27.308 --> 00:12:30.603
About an hour.

116
00:12:31.771 --> 00:12:33.689
You should start your homework.

117
00:12:34.649 --> 00:12:39.278
I promise to tell you all about it
when I see you. I love you. Bye.

118
00:12:40.821 --> 00:12:45.868
That was my son, Charlie.
He's 8. He'll be 9 next week.

119
00:12:46.285 --> 00:12:50.331
I'm Paul Martel.
I'll be 28 in July.

120
00:12:50.790 --> 00:12:55.169
I'm Constance.
And I’m late. I have to go.

121
00:12:55.836 --> 00:12:59.674
Before you go, take a book.

122
00:12:59.840 --> 00:13:04.387
No.
I couldn't.

123
00:13:04.679 --> 00:13:08.140
Sure you can.
A souvenir.

124
00:13:08.349 --> 00:13:11.852
Go down there.
You know, like before.

125
00:13:12.103 --> 00:13:13.979
Okay.

126
00:13:21.861 --> 00:13:25.323
Keep going.
Stop.

127
00:13:25.824 --> 00:13:27.367
Now right.

128
00:13:27.617 --> 00:13:29.828
No, right.

129
00:13:31.036 --> 00:13:35.165
Okay, now the second
shelf from the top...

130
00:13:35.332 --> 00:13:38.168
take the fourth one from the left.

131
00:13:38.377 --> 00:13:40.337
Got it?

132
00:13:40.838 --> 00:13:44.133
-Think so.
-Open to page 23.

133
00:13:52.433 --> 00:13:56.854
<i>"Drink wine, this is life eternal</i>

134
00:13:57.021 --> 00:14:00.398
<i>This, all that youth will give to you</i>

135
00:14:00.565 --> 00:14:05.403
<i>It is the season for wine, roses
And drunken friends</i>

136
00:14:05.570 --> 00:14:07.697
<i>Be happy for this moment</i>

137
00:14:07.864 --> 00:14:11.367
-<i>This moment is your life"</i>
-This moment is your life.

138
00:14:19.876 --> 00:14:23.588
I have to go.
Thank you.

139
00:14:23.796 --> 00:14:27.425
PAUL: Can you find your way out?
-I hope so.

140
00:14:29.552 --> 00:14:31.471
That's my bedroom.

141
00:14:34.264 --> 00:14:37.809
It was nice meeting you, Constance.

142
00:14:38.435 --> 00:14:42.439
Come back if you need more books
or medical attention.

143
00:14:42.606 --> 00:14:43.648
[DOOR CLOSES]

144
00:14:55.035 --> 00:14:56.243
CONNIE:
Hey!

145
00:15:06.295 --> 00:15:07.338
Ooh.

146
00:15:08.381 --> 00:15:09.589
Ooh!

147
00:15:15.470 --> 00:15:16.805
Ooh.

148
00:15:21.267 --> 00:15:23.478
CONNIE: Hey, Glo.
-Hey.

149
00:15:24.270 --> 00:15:28.483
-That wouldn't be the TV on, would it?
-I was just turning it off.

150
00:15:28.983 --> 00:15:32.362
Sure you were.
Heh, heh, heh.

151
00:15:34.906 --> 00:15:36.074
[SIGHS]

152
00:15:36.950 --> 00:15:39.369
-The wind knocked me down.
GLORIA: Oh, yeah?

153
00:15:39.828 --> 00:15:42.288
You all right?
You need anything?

154
00:15:42.497 --> 00:15:48.962
-Whoa. Gross. Were you in a fight?
-No, just fell over.

155
00:15:49.129 --> 00:15:51.338
-Does it hurt?
-Little bit.

156
00:15:51.547 --> 00:15:54.258
-Cool!
-Where are you going?

157
00:15:54.466 --> 00:15:57.219
CHARLIE: To get the camera!
-Try this.

158
00:15:57.386 --> 00:15:58.554
Thank you.

159
00:15:59.846 --> 00:16:04.517
-Why do you need the camera?
-It's for school. We're doing blood and stuff.

160
00:16:04.684 --> 00:16:08.020
Okay, now look like it really hurts.

161
00:16:08.271 --> 00:16:09.689
-Ready?
CHARLIE: Yeah.

162
00:16:09.856 --> 00:16:11.816
Ow!

163
00:16:12.817 --> 00:16:14.193
This will be great.

164
00:16:14.777 --> 00:16:18.698
The wind blew her down.
She bled and everything.

165
00:16:18.906 --> 00:16:20.533
Everybody's hats blew off.

166
00:16:20.700 --> 00:16:22.909
Look who's the war photographer.
You okay?

167
00:16:23.160 --> 00:16:25.996
-Yeah. It took me down like an old lady.
-Oh, hey.

168
00:16:26.163 --> 00:16:31.168
CONNIE: It was humiliating.
CHARLIE: Dad, look at the pictures.

169
00:16:31.334 --> 00:16:34.212
EDWARD: At least we got the evidence.
Anyone we can sue?

170
00:16:34.379 --> 00:16:38.340
No. There was this nice guy
who helped me.

171
00:16:38.507 --> 00:16:42.845
It was like this, Dad.
It was a twister. Whoa!

172
00:16:43.846 --> 00:16:47.183
Dad, look.
It was like this.

173
00:16:47.349 --> 00:16:49.560
-Wow.
CHARLIE: It's a tornado.

174
00:16:49.727 --> 00:16:55.232
He lived around there. He got me
some Band-Aids and put me in a taxi.

175
00:16:55.399 --> 00:16:57.568
Was he good-looking?

176
00:17:00.571 --> 00:17:01.906
I feel sick.

177
00:17:02.615 --> 00:17:07.203
-You do your homework?
-I can't. I don't know how to do it.

178
00:17:07.453 --> 00:17:11.582
Come on, I'll help you.
Then you can help me with mine.

179
00:17:11.749 --> 00:17:14.752
Did you get his name, this guy?

180
00:17:14.960 --> 00:17:17.713
We could send him a bottle of wine.

181
00:17:18.214 --> 00:17:19.422
Cheap wine.

182
00:17:19.589 --> 00:17:21.798
[CHUCKLES]

183
00:17:35.896 --> 00:17:39.149
EDWARD: Con, stand there a second.
Wait a minute.

184
00:17:39.733 --> 00:17:43.362
Stay there a second.
I'm trying to figure out the....

185
00:17:44.112 --> 00:17:48.283
The thing I can't figure out
is the zoom-thing.

186
00:17:48.450 --> 00:17:50.911
There it is.
Okay, hold on, stay there.

187
00:17:51.078 --> 00:17:55.290
Got the zoomy-thingy zooming.

188
00:17:57.292 --> 00:18:02.089
Stay there. I'm trying to figure
this out. I wanna see if it focuses.

189
00:18:02.506 --> 00:18:04.925
Hold on.
Here.

190
00:18:06.927 --> 00:18:08.887
Cool.
Very cool.

191
00:18:09.096 --> 00:18:12.307
So beautiful.
If you only knew.

192
00:18:12.516 --> 00:18:16.603
Look at you.
God, what a beauty.

193
00:18:18.105 --> 00:18:19.897
[CONNIE GIGGLING]

194
00:18:25.444 --> 00:18:27.947
Something the matter?

195
00:18:30.156 --> 00:18:36.621
-Nothing. Nothing at all.
-Good. Come here.

196
00:18:51.344 --> 00:18:55.807
EDWARD: This is really good.
-No, it isn't. Go away.

197
00:19:00.353 --> 00:19:05.524
I think I'm really zooming.
I found the zoom. Found it.

198
00:19:05.733 --> 00:19:07.818
CHARLIE:
Dad.

199
00:19:08.027 --> 00:19:10.321
-Shit.
CHARLIE: Mom.

200
00:19:10.654 --> 00:19:13.823
I can't sleep.

201
00:19:15.033 --> 00:19:16.451
CONNIE:
Jesus.

202
00:19:17.743 --> 00:19:21.747
I’ll be back. I'll be back.
Don't fall asleep.

203
00:19:22.039 --> 00:19:23.206
CONNIE:
It works.

204
00:19:29.004 --> 00:19:32.883
Mom, are you nuts?
You forgot my lunch.

205
00:19:33.342 --> 00:19:37.387
I did not. It's by the door.
Come with me.

206
00:19:37.554 --> 00:19:40.599
-What are you chewing?
-Nothing.

207
00:19:40.849 --> 00:19:43.518
Spit that out.
What is that?

208
00:19:44.602 --> 00:19:48.522
-Ugh. That's lovely.
-Mom?

209
00:19:48.689 --> 00:19:51.400
CONNIE: Yes?
-I don't want to be a dumb bunny.

210
00:19:51.567 --> 00:19:56.530
CONNIE: Honey, it's a play. There's
lots of other bunnies. It'll be cool.

211
00:19:57.031 --> 00:19:59.575
CHARLIE: You're bonkers, Mom.
-So you tell me.

212
00:19:59.784 --> 00:20:02.411
CHARLIE: Love you.
-Love you too. What's that?

213
00:20:02.578 --> 00:20:05.206
CHARLIE:
Oh. Thank you.

214
00:20:08.876 --> 00:20:09.919
Bye.

215
00:22:05.034 --> 00:22:07.036
[LINE RINGING]

216
00:22:09.538 --> 00:22:10.914
[CLEARS THROAT]

217
00:22:15.335 --> 00:22:17.462
PAUL [ON RECORDING]:
Hi, this is Paul Martel.

218
00:22:17.629 --> 00:22:20.422
Leave a message after the beep.
Thanks.

219
00:22:21.757 --> 00:22:23.425
PAUL:
Hello? Hello?

220
00:22:24.009 --> 00:22:25.260
-Hello?
-Hello?

221
00:22:25.427 --> 00:22:28.680
Hello.
You're there.

222
00:22:28.847 --> 00:22:32.434
This is Connie Sumner,
the one from the windy day.

223
00:22:32.684 --> 00:22:35.229
Oh, that one.

224
00:22:36.188 --> 00:22:38.190
How's the knee?
Did you ice it?

225
00:22:38.565 --> 00:22:42.569
Yes, I iced it and I elevated it.
You name it, I did it.

226
00:22:42.778 --> 00:22:48.157
It's much better.
I just wanted to call and thank you.

227
00:22:48.366 --> 00:22:51.077
I wanted your address
because I wanted to send you a bottle--

228
00:22:51.285 --> 00:22:53.079
-Where are you?
-What?

229
00:22:53.246 --> 00:22:55.581
I said, where are you?

230
00:22:58.376 --> 00:23:01.753
I'm in Grand Central.
It's really hard to hear you.

231
00:23:02.045 --> 00:23:04.673
-Come and see me.
-What?

232
00:23:04.881 --> 00:23:08.260
Yeah, take a break.
I'll make you some coffee.

233
00:23:11.721 --> 00:23:13.681
Coffee?

234
00:23:17.309 --> 00:23:22.398
-Um.... Okay.
-Okay.

235
00:23:22.773 --> 00:23:24.400
See you.
Bye.

236
00:23:24.567 --> 00:23:26.235
Fuck.

237
00:23:29.947 --> 00:23:31.866
[FOOTSTEPS]

238
00:23:32.032 --> 00:23:34.660
[CONNIE GRUNTING]

239
00:23:37.788 --> 00:23:40.749
No permanent damage, I see.

240
00:23:43.627 --> 00:23:48.299
-We take Medicaid, Blue Cross....
-I’m uninsured.

241
00:23:49.216 --> 00:23:52.595
No. I'm afraid we don't
take charity cases.

242
00:23:57.474 --> 00:23:59.518
It was a joke.

243
00:24:07.818 --> 00:24:11.113
Look at this.
Jack London.

244
00:24:11.280 --> 00:24:15.159
First edition of White Fang,
in the original dust jacket.

245
00:24:15.951 --> 00:24:18.203
And I got it for a buck-fifty.

246
00:24:18.370 --> 00:24:22.541
-What's it worth?
-About 4000 times more.

247
00:24:26.294 --> 00:24:31.382
