You okay?

754
01:26:22.282 --> 01:26:25.327
♪<i>All along the way</i>♪

755
01:26:25.494 --> 01:26:28.079
♪<i>Hiding on the sideline</i>♪

756
01:26:28.704 --> 01:26:34.293
♪<i>They must be the ones
Who have never dreamed at all</i>♪

757
01:26:35.002 --> 01:26:37.838
♪<i>Catch a star from the sky</i>♪

758
01:26:38.005 --> 01:26:41.300
♪<i>Let it sparkle in your eye</i>♪

759
01:26:41.467 --> 01:26:44.804
♪<i>Set your sights above the crowd</i>♪

760
01:26:44.971 --> 01:26:47.640
[CHILDREN SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

761
01:26:52.478 --> 01:26:57.608
♪<i>What's the sense in dreaming
If your dreams are small?</i>♪

762
01:26:57.775 --> 01:27:03.489
♪<i>What's the sense in walking
If you don't walk tall?</i>♪

763
01:27:21.424 --> 01:27:24.009
[SINGING INAUDIBLY]

764
01:27:53.330 --> 01:27:56.499
You were spectacular,
you know that?

765
01:27:56.875 --> 01:27:59.002
-Wasn't he great?
EDWARD: Great.

766
01:28:00.003 --> 01:28:02.212
He was great.
Great.

767
01:28:02.880 --> 01:28:04.340
Really great.

768
01:28:05.049 --> 01:28:10.179
I have to help clean up. I'll kiss
you good night when I get home, okay?

769
01:28:11.387 --> 01:28:13.931
[TIRES SCREECHING THEN CRASHING]

770
01:28:18.353 --> 01:28:22.273
-Sorry, Ed. Looks like I nailed you.
EDWARD: It's all right.

771
01:28:23.775 --> 01:28:25.860
It's all right, Jerry.

772
01:28:32.407 --> 01:28:34.618
You better check to see
if this will open.

773
01:28:34.785 --> 01:28:38.205
No, no. It's nothing.
This is fine.

774
01:28:42.918 --> 01:28:47.381
-Did he dent you, Dad?
-Yes, he did. Yes.

775
01:28:47.547 --> 01:28:49.800
Can we call the cops, Dad?

776
01:28:51.885 --> 01:28:54.805
-Sure you don't wanna check the trunk?
-We'll deal with it tomorrow.

777
01:28:55.055 --> 01:28:57.391
-It'll just take a second.
-No!

778
01:30:14.009 --> 01:30:16.178
[GROANS]

779
01:30:32.152 --> 01:30:34.196
[GAGS]

780
01:32:03.410 --> 01:32:04.578
Oh, my God.

781
01:32:04.744 --> 01:32:09.207
Charlie, look at your dad
and tell me what's wrong.

782
01:32:11.334 --> 01:32:12.794
What?

783
01:32:14.421 --> 01:32:17.924
His shoes.
They're different colors.

784
01:32:25.807 --> 01:32:27.809
Honey, you look awful.

785
01:32:27.976 --> 01:32:32.355
What happened last night? Did you sleep?
I got up and looked for you.

786
01:32:32.606 --> 01:32:34.316
I just...

787
01:32:35.775 --> 01:32:36.818
..got some air.

788
01:32:37.777 --> 01:32:39.737
Are you okay?

789
01:32:40.779 --> 01:32:41.989
Yeah.

790
01:32:54.043 --> 01:32:55.835
Do you like it here?

791
01:32:56.294 --> 01:32:59.547
What?
Of course I like it here.

792
01:32:59.839 --> 01:33:04.052
We don't have to stay here.
We can move back to the city.

793
01:33:05.344 --> 01:33:08.805
Honey, what has gotten into you?

794
01:33:10.181 --> 01:33:12.308
Are you okay?

795
01:33:12.475 --> 01:33:15.353
Yeah, yeah.
I'm fine. Fine.

796
01:33:17.688 --> 01:33:20.816
-Are you okay?
-I’m fine.

797
01:33:22.068 --> 01:33:25.780
Everybody's fine.
And we're not moving anywhere.

798
01:34:08.239 --> 01:34:10.700
CHARLIE:
The cops are here, Mom.

799
01:34:11.867 --> 01:34:15.079
-What do they want?
-I'm sure it's nothing.

800
01:34:21.877 --> 01:34:23.837
CHARLIE:
N.Y.P.D., Mom.

801
01:34:26.046 --> 01:34:27.756
CONNIE: Hello?
DEAN: Mrs. Sumner?

802
01:34:27.923 --> 01:34:29.758
-Yes.
-I’m Detective Dean.

803
01:34:29.925 --> 01:34:32.052
This is Detective Mirojnick, N.Y.P.D.

804
01:34:32.219 --> 01:34:33.762
Something happen?
Is something wrong?

805
01:34:33.929 --> 01:34:37.766
Oh, no.
Do you know a Paul Martel?

806
01:34:38.100 --> 01:34:43.981
-Yes, not very well. Why?
-Do you know where he is?

807
01:34:45.232 --> 01:34:46.900
No.

808
01:34:47.943 --> 01:34:51.405
At home, I would imagine.

809
01:34:51.572 --> 01:34:53.407
Do you know where he lives?

810
01:34:53.574 --> 01:34:55.659
SoHo, isn't it?

811
01:34:56.660 --> 01:35:00.372
Your name and number
were found on his desk.

812
01:35:01.498 --> 01:35:03.834
-Has he done something wrong?
-We don't know.

813
01:35:04.001 --> 01:35:06.794
He's been reported
missing by his family.

814
01:35:06.961 --> 01:35:09.464
His wife doesn't know where he is.

815
01:35:12.300 --> 01:35:14.761
I didn't know he was married.

816
01:35:15.386 --> 01:35:16.637
Separated.

817
01:35:21.600 --> 01:35:23.685
When did you see him last?

818
01:35:23.894 --> 01:35:27.814
I don't know, it’s hard to say.

819
01:35:30.275 --> 01:35:31.818
He's a book dealer.

820
01:35:31.985 --> 01:35:35.113
I barely know him.
I was going to buy books from him.

821
01:35:35.614 --> 01:35:39.326
-And did you?
-No, not yet.

822
01:35:41.911 --> 01:35:44.830
Has something happened?
You think he's all right?

823
01:35:44.997 --> 01:35:47.666
It's hard to say at this point.

824
01:35:47.833 --> 01:35:49.835
We're working on it.

825
01:35:51.295 --> 01:35:55.174
-Anyway, thanks. Thanks for your time.
CONNIE: Thank you.

826
01:35:55.424 --> 01:35:59.470
I like these snow-glass things.
My boy has some of these.

827
01:35:59.637 --> 01:36:03.474
-If you hear from Mr. Martel, let us know.
-Certainly.

828
01:36:31.085 --> 01:36:33.379
Dad!
Cops came to our house today.

829
01:36:35.840 --> 01:36:37.508
Cops?
What did they want?

830
01:36:42.221 --> 01:36:43.264
Someone's missing.

831
01:36:43.722 --> 01:36:46.683
And they have to check everyone,
you know.

832
01:36:51.020 --> 01:36:52.063
Who was it?

833
01:36:53.355 --> 01:36:55.524
Honey, sit up straight.

834
01:36:58.235 --> 01:37:01.530
-Who was it?
-I don't think you know him.

835
01:37:01.697 --> 01:37:03.740
-He sells books.
-Oh.

836
01:37:03.907 --> 01:37:05.909
I forget where I met him.

837
01:37:06.743 --> 01:37:09.246
Was it a bad guy, Mom?

838
01:37:11.623 --> 01:37:13.750
Why did they want to talk to you?

839
01:37:13.917 --> 01:37:18.297
I guess he had my name and number.

840
01:37:19.631 --> 01:37:22.759
Why would he have your number?

841
01:37:23.427 --> 01:37:25.721
I think I bought a book from him.

842
01:37:38.066 --> 01:37:41.235
-Be careful. Take it easy.
BOY: Hey, Charlie!

843
01:37:41.569 --> 01:37:44.447
Oh, my darling.
Oh, I wished you lived closer.

844
01:37:48.784 --> 01:37:53.247
Lord, bless this food to our use,
and us to thy service.

845
01:37:53.956 --> 01:37:58.294
And help us be ever mindful
of the needs of others. Amen.

846
01:37:58.461 --> 01:38:00.630
GROUP:
Amen.

847
01:38:00.796 --> 01:38:02.590
MAN:
Very nice, Edward.

848
01:38:12.933 --> 01:38:14.267
GROUP:
All right!

849
01:38:22.984 --> 01:38:26.821
I have a story you don't know
about Edward. Gather close.

850
01:39:14.703 --> 01:39:16.705
DEAN:
Hello, Mrs. Sumner.

851
01:39:16.871 --> 01:39:21.001
Sorry to bother you on the weekend.
I'm Detective Dean.

852
01:39:21.167 --> 01:39:23.670
-This is Detective Mirojnick, N.Y.P.D.
EDWARD: Okay.

853
01:39:23.837 --> 01:39:27.090
We were hoping to talk
to you for a few minutes.

854
01:39:27.257 --> 01:39:28.841
EDWARD:
Sure.

855
01:39:29.008 --> 01:39:31.885
-Charlie, we're going up on the porch.
-Can I come?

856
01:39:32.136 --> 01:39:33.344
EDWARD: No.
-No, sweetheart.

857
01:39:33.511 --> 01:39:36.431
Stay out here.
Play with Poppy, we'll be right back.

858
01:39:37.223 --> 01:39:41.184
DEAN: I don't know if your wife
mentioned, we were here a week ago.

859
01:39:41.351 --> 01:39:42.686
About Paul Martel.

860
01:39:42.853 --> 01:39:44.771
Yeah, the man who was missing.

861
01:39:44.938 --> 01:39:50.694
Well, he's not missing anymore.
His body was discovered last weekend.

862
01:39:51.194 --> 01:39:53.154
God, that's terrible.

863
01:39:56.073 --> 01:39:57.283
Oh, my God.

864
01:39:57.450 --> 01:40:01.871
MIROJNICK: Do you recall where
you met Mr. Martel, Mrs. Sumner?

865
01:40:02.455 --> 01:40:05.248
-I told you.
-No, ma'am, you didn't.

866
01:40:05.415 --> 01:40:07.459
I'm sorry.

867
01:40:07.667 --> 01:40:09.543
I can't remember.

868
01:40:10.085 --> 01:40:12.045
A fundraiser, I think.

869
01:40:12.211 --> 01:40:13.963
MIROJNICK:
Can you be more specific?

870
01:40:14.172 --> 01:40:15.214
Juilliard.

871
01:40:17.467 --> 01:40:18.593
Juilliard?

872
01:40:19.469 --> 01:40:20.595
The music school.

873
01:40:21.429 --> 01:40:25.266
-Yes, I know what Juilliard is.
-Of course you do. I'm sorry.

874
01:40:25.475 --> 01:40:27.684
MIROJNICK:
Were you there too, sir?

875
01:40:29.102 --> 01:40:31.938
Yes.
Yes, I think I was.

876
01:40:32.105 --> 01:40:34.608
DEAN:
Well, maybe you met Mr. Martel.

877
01:40:36.234 --> 01:40:38.194
No.
No, not that I remember.

878
01:40:38.402 --> 01:40:40.613
Maybe you'd recognize him.

879
01:40:41.572 --> 01:40:43.741
No, I've never met him before.

880
01:40:43.908 --> 01:40:46.701
-Is that him?
-Yes. Yes.

881
01:40:47.577 --> 01:40:50.246
MIROJNICK:
You ever been to his apartment?

882
01:40:50.413 --> 01:40:51.831
No.

883
01:40:51.998 --> 01:40:53.750
No, I hardly knew him.

884
01:40:53.917 --> 01:40:57.796
-I didn't know why he had my number.
-Maybe he liked you.

885
01:40:57.962 --> 01:40:59.798
Look, that's enough.

886
01:41:03.134 --> 01:41:06.805
So you've never been to his apartment.
How about the neighborhood?

887
01:41:06.971 --> 01:41:08.723
-Hang out down there?
-No.

888
01:41:08.932 --> 01:41:10.683
No, not often...

889
01:41:10.850 --> 01:41:11.934
...Oh no, never.

890
01:41:12.101 --> 01:41:15.979
Never. I can't remember the
last time I was in SoHo.

891
01:41:16.146 --> 01:41:18.273
It was four weeks ago, actually.

892
01:41:21.026 --> 01:41:25.322
You got a parking ticket in front
of Martel's apartment, four weeks ago.

893
01:41:25.489 --> 01:41:30.786
Oh, that. Right. I had coffee
with friends at a little place.

894
01:41:30.953 --> 01:41:32.121
I forgot.

895
01:41:32.287 --> 01:41:35.374
-It was Tracy and Sally.
-Oh, yeah. Yes. Yep.

896
01:41:47.386 --> 01:41:49.471
EDWARD:
Look...

897
01:41:50.555 --> 01:41:54.058
...my wife has told you everything
she knows, so have I.

898
01:41:54.976 --> 01:41:57.645
If you don't mind,
we'd like to get back to our son.

899
01:41:57.812 --> 01:41:59.647
All right.

900
01:41:59.814 --> 01:42:04.318
-Why don't I give you my card?
-I have your card.

901
01:42:05.361 --> 01:42:07.071
Right.

902
01:42:08.197 --> 01:42:10.658
-Enjoy your weekend.
-You too.

903
01:43:06.088 --> 01:43:08.382
Sumner, please.

904
01:43:47.171 --> 01:43:48.631
Oh, my God.

905
01:43:50.174 --> 01:43:51.676
Connie?

906
01:43:53.094 --> 01:43:54.762
Hi, Tracy.

907
01:43:54.929 --> 01:43:58.140
I'm just picking up
my silk suit for tonight.

908
01:44:00.100 --> 01:44:02.185
I was thinking of wearing the black.

909
01:44:11.820 --> 01:44:13.320
[MACHINE HISSING]

910
01:44:14.988 --> 01:44:20.493
I'm giving it to Goodwill. Let someone
else be gorgeous for a change. Heh, heh.

911
01:44:23.705 --> 01:44:27.625
What should we bring, aside
from our sparkling personalities?

912
01:44:31.462 --> 01:44:34.173
EDWARD: How we doing?
CONNIE: Fine.

913
01:44:34.340 --> 01:44:37.635
-Need help?
-No.

914
01:44:39.011 --> 01:44:43.974
Well, the white is not cold,
so I'm gonna put it in the freezer.

915
01:44:45.017 --> 01:44:47.810
Just remind me it's in there,
all right?

916
01:44:49.854 --> 01:44:52.523
Most people drink red anyway.

917
01:44:56.527 --> 01:45:00.239
I love these things. Is there any
place you guys haven't been?

918
01:45:00.406 --> 01:45:02.908
The Rosenthals got
795 for their place.

919
01:45:03.075 --> 01:45:06.996
-In two days they had six offers.
JEFF: Sealed bids is how they do it.

920
01:45:07.163 --> 01:45:09.832
What do you think
this place is worth, Ed?

921
01:45:09.999 --> 01:45:13.544
I don't know. If you sell
your house, where do you go?

922
01:45:13.711 --> 01:45:17.048
BETH: At those prices, Tahiti.
JOSH: Bangkok.

923
01:45:17.214 --> 01:45:19.799
Connie, where is this one from?

924
01:45:30.018 --> 01:45:31.894
Fiji.

925
01:45:32.519 --> 01:45:35.564
BETH: Remember, Jeff,
I asked you to take me to Fiji.

926
01:45:35.731 --> 01:45:40.527
And then you took me to Hawaii.
We went fishing every single....

927
01:45:41.111 --> 01:45:43.197
[CHATTERING]

928
01:46:03.550 --> 01:46:05.886
What happened, Edward?

929
01:46:07.971 --> 01:46:10.057
What did you do?

930
01:46:11.392 --> 01:46:12.935
Did you hurt him?

931
01:46:14.603 --> 01:46:16.230
Huh?

932
01:46:17.481 --> 01:46:18.941
Edward?

933
01:46:20.359 --> 01:46:22.277
Did you hurt him?

934
01:46:24.405 --> 01:46:26.115
You did, didn't you?

935
01:46:28.742 --> 01:46:31.286
Jesus, Edward.

936
01:46:32.162 --> 01:46:34.456
Talk to me.

937
01:46:34.623 --> 01:46:36.834
Tell me what you did!

938
01:46:37.000 --> 01:46:40.796
No, you tell me what you did.

939
01:46:41.171 --> 01:46:46.134
How you fucked him, over and over and over.
You lied to me!

940
01:46:46.300 --> 01:46:49.804
-Over and over and over.
-Edward, please--

941
01:46:49.971 --> 01:46:51.931
No, you don't talk to me now.

942
01:46:52.432 --> 01:46:54.809
I gave everything...

943
01:46:55.601 --> 01:46:57.812
...for this family.

944
01:46:58.187 --> 01:46:59.439
Everything.

945
01:47:01.107 --> 01:47:03.401
And what did you do?

946
01:47:04.444 --> 01:47:07.821
You threw it all away,
like it was nothing.

947
01:47:08.655 --> 01:47:10.282
For what?

948
01:47:10.991 --> 01:47:13.200
To the fucking kid.

949
01:47:21.500 --> 01:47:23.627
You didn't think I'd know?

950
01:47:23.794 --> 01:47:27.173
I wouldn't feel it?
I knew it from the very first day.

951
01:47:29.675 --> 01:47:34.180
Because I know you, Connie.
I know you and I fucking hate you.

952
01:47:34.346 --> 01:47:37.975
I didn't want to kill him,
I wanted to kill you!

953
01:47:40.436 --> 01:47:42.645
Oh, my God.

954
01:47:52.822 --> 01:47:56.159
Edward.
Oh, my God.

955
01:48:01.831 --> 01:48:04.208
[CONNIE SOBBING]

956
01:48:07.001 --> 01:48:09.045
EDWARD:
Oh, my God.

957
01:48:50.461 --> 01:48:53.589
Mom, look what I did.

958
01:48:56.342 --> 01:49:00.721
CONNIE:
Honey, it's okay. That's okay.

959
01:49:00.888 --> 01:49:02.306
I'm sorry, Mom.

960
01:49:02.473 --> 01:49:06.477
It's an accident.
Everybody has accidents.

961
01:49:06.644 --> 01:49:08.813
Why aren't you in bed, Mom?

962
01:49:11.982 --> 01:49:13.358
I don't know.

963
01:49:17.612 --> 01:49:19.196
Charlie, look at me.

964
01:49:19.738 --> 01:49:21.907
I want you to know...

965
01:49:22.074 --> 01:49:26.161
...that I love you,
more than anything in the world.

966
01:49:28.455 --> 01:49:31.834
And I want you to know
that your daddy and me both...

967
01:49:32.001 --> 01:49:34.503
…will always, always love you.

968
01:49:34.670 --> 01:49:37.631
No matter what.
Hm?

969
01:49:40.175 --> 01:49:43.012
-Okay?
-Okay.

970
01:49:43.220 --> 01:49:44.263
Come on, sweetie.

971
01:49:45.097 --> 01:49:49.852
Let's go fix up your bed
all nice and fresh, okay?

972
01:49:50.185 --> 01:49:51.896
All right.

973
01:50:34.772 --> 01:50:36.564
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

974
01:53:03.628 --> 01:53:06.047
You can come on up
and clean it off, no?

975
01:53:06.214 --> 01:53:10.718
Come on.
I'm not an ax murderer. I promise.

976
01:53:19.894 --> 01:53:21.521
[INAUDIBLE]
Taxi.

977
01:53:44.418 --> 01:53:47.046
Thank you.

978
01:54:13.114 --> 01:54:15.241
What are we going to do?

979
01:54:18.369 --> 01:54:20.954
I'm so scared.

980
01:54:22.956 --> 01:54:24.248
I’ll turn myself in.

981
01:54:24.957 --> 01:54:26.457
No.

982
01:54:29.294 --> 01:54:30.837
No.

983
01:54:40.180 --> 01:54:42.765
No, we can get through this.

984
01:54:44.141 --> 01:54:46.810
We'll take it one day at a time.

985
01:54:48.562 --> 01:54:50.689
No one will know.

986
01:54:52.399 --> 01:54:54.484
We'll know.

987
01:54:59.573 --> 01:55:00.949
Three thousand.

988
01:55:01.617 --> 01:55:06.246
Three thousand dollars.
3200, 3500, 3800, 4000...

989
01:55:06.413 --> 01:55:08.624
42, 45, 4800!

990
01:56:35.294 --> 01:56:37.587
We can disappear.

991
01:56:39.589 --> 01:56:41.508
We can raise some money.

992
01:56:41.675 --> 01:56:44.844
Sell everything
and just leave the country.

993
01:56:46.304 --> 01:56:47.888
Señorita?

994
01:56:48.806 --> 01:56:50.975
Mexico.

995
01:56:52.393 --> 01:56:54.269
Why not?

996
01:56:55.979 --> 01:56:58.148
We can get a little house
on the beach.

997
01:56:58.773 --> 01:57:00.859
Take a different name.

998
01:57:02.235 --> 01:57:03.945
People do it all the time.

999
01:57:05.071 --> 01:57:07.324
What will we tell Charlie?

1000
01:57:09.159 --> 01:57:11.952
CONNIE:
Tell him it's an adventure.

1001
01:57:14.621 --> 01:57:17.041
We could fish all day.

1002
01:57:20.502 --> 01:57:23.630
We could learn to play the guitar.

1003
01:57:24.922 --> 01:57:29.385
I would serenade you
to sleep every night.

1004
01:57:30.595 --> 01:57:33.972
We'll just live the rest
of our lives on that beach.

1005
01:57:34.473 --> 01:57:37.809
And then when we die,
we can just push out to sea.

1006
01:57:38.310 --> 01:57:39.561
What do you think?

1007
01:57:42.439 --> 01:57:44.399
Sounds perfect.


